- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about a distributed memory parallel programming system for use with MPI.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of the Classdesc reflection system to ease the task of building complicated messages.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possibility as the paper discusses a system for making MPI programming easier and more efficient.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of Classdesc to build complicated messages.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses a system for parallel programming which could be useful in machine learning applications.
